Downloading the Driver install tool (top of the options) from 
    http://support.brother.com/g/b/downloadlist.aspx?c=de&lang=de&prod=hll2300d_us_eu_as&os=128&flang=English
follow the folling steps in the terminal (wherever it was downloaded): 

	$   gunzip lin...[tab]
	$   sudo su 
    #   bash lin...[tab]
		> enter "HL-L2300D" (without quotes)
		> enter "y"
		> enter "y"
		> enter "n" for device URI (because on USB)
		> test print if you like (y) 
		> hit ENTER
		> exit root 
	done 
